And remember, we reviewed examples from Luke 1 and 2 of humble, obedient ones

01:18:47.430 --> 01:18:53.630
that Jehovah appreciated like Mary and the humble shepherds, Simeon and Anna.

01:18:53.630 --> 01:19:01.829
And the encouragement was imitate those fine examples and be the kind of people that Jehovah is pleased to use

01:19:01.829 --> 01:19:05.829
by cultivating what matters most to Jehovah.

01:19:05.829 --> 01:19:13.340
And that is spiritual qualities that he holds dear and that makes us useful to him.

01:19:13.340 --> 01:19:19.699
But the fact is, you are ones that Jehovah is pleased to use.

01:19:19.699 --> 01:19:25.779
In fact, all of Jehovah's people, all in the listening audience, all of Jehovah's people, the world over,

01:19:25.779 --> 01:19:29.100
Jehovah is pleased to use them because he is drawn each one.

01:19:29.100 --> 01:19:32.460
We know that, don't we? John 644 tells us, what does the verse say?

01:19:32.460 --> 01:19:38.659
That no man can come to me unless the father who sent me draws him and I will resurrect him in the last days.

01:19:38.699 --> 01:19:45.979
So Jehovah has drawn each one of us because he saw something in our hearts of value.

01:19:45.979 --> 01:19:53.819
He saw a humility and honesty and a desire to learn the truth and to serve the true and living God.

01:19:53.819 --> 01:20:00.500
And so we have the privilege then of being a part of Jehovah's name people.

01:20:00.500 --> 01:20:06.060
As individuals, we have the privilege of having a place in his great spiritual temple arrangement.

01:20:06.060 --> 01:20:09.500
We are all on Jehovah's team.

01:20:09.500 --> 01:20:17.079
And the privilege that every one of us has, of course, is to bear his name in the kingdom preaching work.

01:20:17.079 --> 01:20:23.319
But at times, Jehovah also gives us other work to do and other assignments that are related to the kingdom preaching work.

01:20:23.319 --> 01:20:29.800
And for you, dear friends, that included providing this training in Gilead.

01:20:29.800 --> 01:20:34.560
And while this Gilead training doesn't place you above your brothers and you certainly do not feel that way,

01:20:34.560 --> 01:20:41.439
it does indicate to Jehovah's approval of you and the fact that he saw something good in your hearts

01:20:41.439 --> 01:20:49.399
that he could then continue to mold and train so that he could use you to further help and strengthen his people.

01:20:49.399 --> 01:20:56.119
And quite likely it's some of the same things that he saw in Mary and the shepherds in Simeon and Anna.

01:20:56.119 --> 01:21:00.119
Humility, deep spirituality, obedience, loyalty,

01:21:00.119 --> 01:21:06.720
appreciation for spiritual things and constancy in your theocratic routine.

01:21:06.720 --> 01:21:18.199
Be assured that Jehovah loves you and that he approves of you for these valuable qualities that really make you useful to him.

01:21:18.199 --> 01:21:26.159
And so our concluding encouragement is keep being the kind of people that Jehovah can use.

01:21:26.159 --> 01:21:29.720
Really, that's at the heart of the encouragement in Philippians 316.

01:21:29.720 --> 01:21:36.800
At any rate to the extent we have made progress, let us go on walking orderly in the same routine.

01:21:36.800 --> 01:21:39.520
And we think back to our examples from Luke 1 and 2.

01:21:39.520 --> 01:21:46.119
And we don't hear again about Simeon and Anna, although we are sure that they remain faithful for the rest of their lives.

01:21:46.119 --> 01:21:54.479
But we do follow Mary as she continued in her service to Jehovah and the years go by as she raised Jesus,

01:21:54.479 --> 01:21:58.880
along with Joseph and her other children who loved and served Jehovah.

01:21:58.880 --> 01:22:10.359
We watched as Mary appreciatively preserved these things in her heart that Jehovah was doing in connection with her son and his son, of course, Jehovah.

01:22:10.359 --> 01:22:17.880
And we also follow Mary as she possibly dealt with the death of her husband at some point along the way.

01:22:17.880 --> 01:22:24.279
And as she dealt with the initial lack of faith of her other children in Jesus Messiah's ship.

01:22:24.279 --> 01:22:31.399
And then finally, as she watched her son die in a most shameful and painful way on that torture state,

01:22:31.399 --> 01:22:37.800
when Simeon's words came true that a long sword would be run through her.

01:22:37.800 --> 01:22:40.880
Jehovah's confidence in Mary was well placed.

01:22:40.880 --> 01:22:45.439
She continued to be the kind of person that he could use.

01:22:45.439 --> 01:22:50.680
And so follow her good example by being one that Jehovah can continue to use,

01:22:50.680 --> 01:22:53.680
by focusing on what matters most to Jehovah.

01:22:53.680 --> 01:22:58.840
Keep cultivating the qualities that will endear you to Jehovah.

01:22:58.840 --> 01:23:04.439
And then whatever work needs to be done, whatever assignment needs to be filled,

01:23:04.439 --> 01:23:07.319
whatever encouragement needs to be given.

01:23:07.319 --> 01:23:14.680
Well, then you will be spiritually qualified and you will be ready to be used by Jehovah if that is his desire.

01:23:14.680 --> 01:23:18.800
As continue to be one that Jehovah would use in his service.

01:23:18.800 --> 01:23:27.199
And then you will always have his favor and you will have joy and contentment in whatever Jehovah has in mind for you to do.

01:23:27.199 --> 01:23:31.800
