01:23:40.079 --> 01:23:45.920
To conclude, our postcard takes us to the southern tip of Africa.

01:23:45.920 --> 01:23:49.279
Welcome to Eswatini.

01:23:49.279 --> 01:23:59.079
This tiny landlocked country, once known as Swaziland, sits between Mozambique and South Africa.

01:23:59.079 --> 01:24:05.359
You can find magnificent wildlife in Shalane National Park.

01:24:05.359 --> 01:24:09.560
Or stand in amazement beside Cebebe Rock.

01:24:09.560 --> 01:24:13.600
One of the world's largest granite domes.

01:24:13.600 --> 01:24:18.960
Tradition has an important place in Eswatini culture.

01:24:18.960 --> 01:24:28.359
How men or women tie Leah fabric over their shoulders communicates whether they are married or single.

01:24:28.359 --> 01:24:34.760
The country also has kept the tradition of an absolute monarchy.

01:24:34.760 --> 01:24:47.159
King Subuza, the second, rained for 82 years until his death in 1982 and had quite the rapport with Jehovah's Witnesses.

01:24:47.159 --> 01:25:00.760
In 1933, the king was delighted with the message carried by pioneers and called his personal bodyguard of 100 warriors to listen as well.

01:25:00.760 --> 01:25:09.239
On another occasion, he offered to buy the loudspeaker and the records our brothers were using.

01:25:09.239 --> 01:25:11.960
They humbly explained,

01:25:11.960 --> 01:25:15.800
It all belongs to another king.

01:25:15.800 --> 01:25:19.960
Subuza wanted to know who this was.

01:25:19.960 --> 01:25:23.000
He is Jesus Christ.

01:25:23.000 --> 01:25:24.600
Subuza replied,

01:25:24.600 --> 01:25:27.880
Oh, he is a great king.

01:25:27.880 --> 01:25:33.000
I don't want to take anything that belongs to him.

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:38.199
Our brothers continue loyally announcing God's kingdom.

01:25:38.199 --> 01:25:45.960
Currently, there are over 3,000 publishers conducting over 4,000 Bible studies.

01:25:45.960 --> 01:25:55.560
The country also hosts refugees from Burundi, Rwanda, Uganda, and various other countries.

01:25:55.560 --> 01:26:03.239
And publishers go to the camp to preach extending a warm welcome and a message of hope.

01:26:03.239 --> 01:26:11.720
You can feel the love our brothers in the Nunguyoyo congregation have for neighbor and each other.

01:26:11.720 --> 01:26:15.319
They wish to send that love to you.

